assessment_details.task_description:
This assessment task has a strong reflective component. Your reflections need to:

contain detailed descriptions of incidents/issues/challenges/successes you encountered during your workplace experience, and how you reacted to them;

discuss your frustrations and consequent growth with regards to the i ncidents/issues/ challenges/successes you chose to document;

ask probing questions about yourself and your future work options;

reflect on how your workplace experience may impact your future career choices.

PART 1: OVERVIEW OF THE WORKPLACE EXPERIENCE (300 to 600 words)

Provide a brief overview focused on the following:

Yourself, your major, your career plans at this stage;

Your motivational style, personality type, conflict resolution style (you may use and refer to the measures/instruments in the Measures folder on BlackBoard);

Dates of internship;

Your placement organisation, including its size, structure, industry, brief history, and culture (you may use and refer to the culture diagnostic in the Measures folder on BlackBoard) ;

Your supervisor - their position in the organisation, their supervisory style (participative, democratic etc);

Tasks/projects allocated, their value (or not) as a learning and development opportunity; and

Your expectations about the graduate attributes required for the placement upon starting the placement, as opposed to the realities after settling into the placement.

PART 2: JOURNAL REFLECTIONS (400-600 words per journal entry)

NOTE: You are required to complete three (3) formative reflective journal entries. You will need to seek timely feedback from fellow students, a mentor, or someone you have worked with as you complete reflections. After consideration of the feedback you received and incorporating comments/suggestions, you need to CHOOSE ONE ENTRY for inclusion in your summative assessment.

Following are some themes that might be used for the journal entries:

the organisation, its culture, and its style of supervision;

how you used your knowledge and attributes;

challenging work tasks;

how you developed your graduate attributes;

how you developed your employability through requesting and responding to feedback;

the role and support of your supervisor;

the role and support of your colleagues;

your role and how you support others and add value;

how you are reacting to being managed by your supervisor and others;

the type of work you have been undertaking, and whether this is the type of work for the next stage of your career.

Journal entry #1: U sing (and justifying your choice of) the SEAL or 4R method, r eflect on your INITIAL workplace experiences regarding your developing employability skill-set.

Look at the graduate attributes indicated on the ECP and discuss the graduate attributes and skills that you brought with you to the workplace and how you used them. You should also research and determine appropriate graduate attributes for your profession. Be sure to communicate your reflection as a specialist in your professional area of expertise.

Journal entry #2 : Again, using (and justifying your choice of) the SEAL or 4R method, reflect on another workplace experience but this time, choose one where you experienced a FAILURE .

Critically evaluate your performance, reflect on what you learned from this experience, and indicate how this experience and learning has assisted you with your developing employability skill-set and relates to appropriate graduate attributes for your profession . Be sure to communicate your reflection as a specialist in your professional area of expertise.

Journal entry #3 : Again, using (and justifying your choice of) the SEAL or 4R method, reflect on a workplace experience, this time with a focus on one where you achieved SUCCESS .

Critically evaluate your performance, reflect on what you learned from this experience, and indicate how this experience and learning has assisted you with your developing employability skill-set and relates to appropriate graduate attributes for your profession . Be sure to communicate your reflection as a specialist in your professional area of expertise,

PART 3: KEY LEARNINGS (100-200 words)

Finally, provide a short summary paragraph that highlights three (3) key lessons learned so far: Two lessons about yourself, and one lesson about the nature of work and organisations.

REFERENCING:

Use a standard referencing system (eg, APA, Harvard)

Include a reference list of all cited literature

Incorporate a minimum of 6 relevant academic references.
